data.enText: a place to which sb/sth is going or being sent
popular holiday destinations like the Bahamas
data.chText: 像巴哈马那样深受大众喜爱的度假胜地

data.enText: Our luggage was checked all the way through to our final destination .
data.chText: 我们的行李一直被托运到最终目的地。

data.enText: a hotel, store, etc. that people will make a special trip to visit
data.chText: 作为目的地的（旅馆、商店、饭店等）

simple_means.memory_skill: destin(e) 注定 + -ation 名词后缀

means: 作为目的地的(旅馆、商店、饭店等)

tr: the ultimate goal for which something is done
written directions for finding some location
written on letters or packages that are to be delivered to that location
the place designated as the end (as of a race or journey)
example: a crowd assembled at the finish
he was nearly exhausted as their destination came into view

example.ex: Spain is still our most popular holiday destination...
example.tran: 西班牙仍是我们最喜爱的度假去处。

example.ex: Only half of the emergency supplies have reached their destination.
example.tran: 仅有一半的紧急救援物资运抵了目的地。

value.def: The destination of someone or something is the place to which they are going or being sent.
